page.title: 01WAMBROOKS/NARFORDS AREA
page.content: This area has no main large towns and no main roads cross it.There are a number of small settlements including Wambrook and Narfords.There is a heavy scattering of farms across the whole area.The county boundary between Somerset and Devon runs East to West across the block.There is a complex network of lanes covering the whole area.Most of it is farmland which reaches a height of 204 metres,there is also about 2 sq.kilometres of woodland.A tributary of the River Axe runs North to South across the square.
